00:53:12.690 --> 00:53:14.300
as opposed to just sort of slumping over,

00:53:14.300 --> 00:53:16.500
which is what you'd expect
wet stuff to do anyway.

00:53:16.500 --> 00:53:18.470
Anyway, the science is nuts.

00:53:18.470 --> 00:53:21.160
I mean there is no known geology

00:53:21.160 --> 00:53:23.440
that would fit this model of Grand Canyon

00:53:23.440 --> 00:53:26.650
and that would be true of their astronomy

00:53:26.650 --> 00:53:27.626
and everything else.

00:53:27.626 --> 00:53:31.080
NCSE has got lots of resources

00:53:31.080 --> 00:53:33.313
as to why creation science is bad.

00:53:35.265 --> 00:53:39.270
But you know, arguing factual information

00:53:39.270 --> 00:53:43.600
is not actually going to
persuade a creationist

00:53:43.600 --> 00:53:46.110
that their science is bad

00:53:47.050 --> 00:53:49.523
because that's not the
most important issue.

00:53:50.540 --> 00:53:53.550
There is considerable literature
studying decision making

00:53:53.550 --> 00:53:56.040
that contends that factual information,

00:53:56.040 --> 00:53:58.270
while not irrelevant, is not primary

00:53:58.270 --> 00:54:00.220
and persuading people
to change their minds.

00:54:00.220 --> 00:54:02.530
And I talked about this
in more detail yesterday.

00:54:02.530 --> 00:54:04.630
If you were here yesterday, thank you.

00:54:04.630 --> 00:54:06.870
I'm not going to repeat
it, but in general,

00:54:06.870 --> 00:54:10.950
for our purposes, lots of these concepts

00:54:12.180 --> 00:54:14.740
from the psychology of belief literature

00:54:14.740 --> 00:54:18.080
explaining why factual
knowledge is rejected,

00:54:18.080 --> 00:54:22.030
they all deal with looking
at factual knowledge

00:54:22.030 --> 00:54:24.210
through an ideological values

00:54:24.210 --> 00:54:26.230
or a group identification filter.

00:54:26.230 --> 00:54:29.040
And the filter comes first and usually,

00:54:29.040 --> 00:54:32.730
that keeps the correct
information, shall we say,

00:54:32.730 --> 00:54:34.113
from being accepted.

00:54:35.000 --> 00:54:37.710
Values, ideology and identification

00:54:37.710 --> 00:54:41.720
are precisely the elements of myth.

00:54:41.720 --> 00:54:44.820
Myth is powerful and creationism is mythic

00:54:44.820 --> 00:54:46.900
in exactly this fashion.

00:54:46.900 --> 00:54:49.530
It reinforces the values, ideology

00:54:49.530 --> 00:54:52.460
and identification of
conservative Christians.

00:54:52.460 --> 00:54:54.780
It's not a surprise then that creationists

00:54:54.780 --> 00:54:56.990
are resistant to accepting evolution.

00:54:56.990 --> 00:55:00.130
If evolution is true, they lose big.

00:55:00.130 --> 00:55:04.003
Obviously they're not going
to just suddenly decide.

00:55:07.870 --> 00:55:10.036
Still, evolution needs to be taught

00:55:10.036 --> 00:55:13.920
so that students are
scientifically literate.

00:55:13.920 --> 00:55:15.820
How can we make this happen?

00:55:15.820 --> 00:55:19.560
I see a short term solution
and a longterm solution.

00:55:19.560 --> 00:55:22.930
The longterm solution relies
on evolution, if you will,

00:55:22.930 --> 00:55:25.460
that like the rest of Christianity,

00:55:25.460 --> 00:55:27.980
conservative Christians
will gradually moderate

00:55:27.980 --> 00:55:30.360
their views regarding evolution.

00:55:30.360 --> 00:55:32.300
The National Center for Science Education

00:55:32.300 --> 00:55:33.920
Voices for Evolution book

00:55:33.920 --> 00:55:36.410
lists statements from
religious organizations

00:55:36.410 --> 00:55:38.890
and other institutions that encourage

00:55:38.890 --> 00:55:40.990
the teaching of evolution in schools.

00:55:40.990 --> 00:55:43.100
These are catholic and
mainstream protestants

00:55:43.100 --> 00:55:44.792
and Jewish groups.

00:55:44.792 --> 00:55:47.870
Theistic evolution, the
theological position

00:55:47.870 --> 00:55:51.130
that evolution occurred, it
was part of God's plan, etc

00:55:51.130 --> 00:55:53.910
is the majority view
in Christianity today.

00:55:53.910 --> 00:55:57.020
It's the theologically
conservative denominations

00:55:57.020 --> 00:55:59.000
that have problems with evolution.

00:55:59.000 --> 00:56:01.540
Most Baptists, Pentecostalists,

00:56:01.540 --> 00:56:05.330
Holiness groups, Charismatics,
Seventh Day Adventists,

00:56:05.330 --> 00:56:07.990
Jehovah's witnesses, and the like.

00:56:07.990 --> 00:56:10.110
But this is not a solid block.

00:56:10.110 --> 00:56:13.270
There are evangelical Christians
who have worked diligently

00:56:13.270 --> 00:56:16.000
to see that evolution gets
taught in their local communities

00:56:16.000 --> 00:56:18.870
and some national
evangelical organizations

00:56:18.870 --> 00:56:21.390
that are very friendly to evolution.

00:56:21.390 --> 00:56:24.800
Biologos is an online evangelical
Christian organization

00:56:24.800 --> 00:56:27.880
and they discuss a variety
of views of evolution,

00:56:27.880 --> 00:56:29.740
believing that it can be harmonized

00:56:29.740 --> 00:56:31.920
with their version of Christianity.

00:56:31.920 --> 00:56:34.230
They talk about the
harmony between science

00:56:34.230 --> 00:56:37.380
and biblical faith as we present

00:56:37.380 --> 00:56:40.290
an evolutionary understanding
of God's creation.

00:56:40.290 --> 00:56:42.407
Another evangelical Christian organization

00:56:42.407 --> 00:56:44.750
is the American Scientific Affiliation

00:56:44.750 --> 00:56:46.090
which similarly supports

00:56:46.090 --> 00:56:48.053
the teaching of evolution in schools.

00:56:49.010 --> 00:56:52.630
The longterm solution to
the anti evolution problem

00:56:52.630 --> 00:56:54.633
in the United States is
for these organizations

00:56:54.633 --> 00:56:57.900
and others and individually
evangelical Christians

00:56:57.900 --> 00:57:00.370
to influence their fellow
conservative Christians

00:57:00.370 --> 00:57:04.200
and persuade them that one
can be a faithful evangelical

00:57:04.200 --> 00:57:06.200
and still accept evolution.

00:57:06.200 --> 00:57:09.120
The way that Biologos or
the ASA would phrase it,

00:57:09.120 --> 00:57:13.283
is that they take the bible
seriously, but not literally.

00:57:15.110 --> 00:57:16.950
The short term situation.

00:57:16.950 --> 00:57:19.923
The short term solution
is to call a truce.

00:57:20.790 --> 00:57:23.020
The big fear of conservative Christians

00:57:23.020 --> 00:57:24.850
is that when their children
are taught evolution,

00:57:24.850 --> 00:57:27.233
they're taught therefore there is no God.

00:57:28.595 --> 00:57:30.960
A number of years ago, a friend of mine

00:57:30.960 --> 00:57:33.720
who was teaching biological anthropology

00:57:33.720 --> 00:57:37.340
at a community college in the southeast,

00:57:37.340 --> 00:57:38.673
we were talking on the phone

00:57:38.673 --> 00:57:41.623
and she said that she had
these kids in her class.

00:57:43.030 --> 00:57:45.510
Young adults, these students
that are undergraduates

00:57:45.510 --> 00:57:49.700
in her class had never
learned evolution at all.

00:57:49.700 --> 00:57:50.533
Full stop.

00:57:50.533 --> 00:57:52.240
Their are teachers they'd
just skip those chapters.

00:57:52.240 --> 00:57:54.040
These kids were tabula rasa.

00:57:54.040 --> 00:57:55.630
The only thing they knew about evolution

00:57:55.630 --> 00:57:58.210
was what they learned on
the street, so to speak.

00:57:58.210 --> 00:58:01.560
This is college, this is
physical anthropology, right?

00:58:01.560 --> 00:58:03.600
So day one you get evolution

00:58:03.600 --> 00:58:06.520
and so she just taught her
class matter of factly,

00:58:06.520 --> 00:58:09.720
like she taught anyplace else

00:58:09.720 --> 00:58:11.790
and after a couple of weeks,

00:58:11.790 --> 00:58:14.240
a couple of these kids came
to talk to her after class

00:58:14.240 --> 00:58:19.010
and they said, well, of course
species change through time.

00:58:19.010 --> 00:58:20.483
You mean that's evolution?

00:58:22.800 --> 00:58:25.400
We thought evolution meant
you can't believe in God.

00:58:28.110 --> 00:58:32.970
I have lots and lots of stories
like that from high school

00:58:32.970 --> 00:58:34.833
as well as university teachers.

00:58:36.370 --> 00:58:40.370
So I would like to assuage
the concerns of parents

00:58:40.370 --> 00:58:42.320
that when their kid walks into,

00:58:42.320 --> 00:58:44.710
especially a high school classroom,

00:58:44.710 --> 00:58:46.430
there is not a teacher there saying,

00:58:46.430 --> 00:58:48.290
okay, take your religion and shove it.

00:58:48.290 --> 00:58:49.540
This just doesn't happen.

00:58:50.710 --> 00:58:53.910
Survey research has
shown that K-12 teachers

00:58:53.910 --> 00:58:57.790
show the same range of religious adherence

00:58:57.790 --> 00:58:58.760
as other Americans.

00:58:58.760 --> 00:59:00.600
In other words, they're highly religious

00:59:00.600 --> 00:59:03.820
about 80 plus percent
of them believe in God,

00:59:03.820 --> 00:59:05.160
most of them are Christian.

00:59:05.160 --> 00:59:08.310
It's highly unlikely
that high school teachers

00:59:08.310 --> 00:59:11.510
are telling kids that they have to choose

00:59:11.510 --> 00:59:13.600
between their faith and science.

00:59:13.600 --> 00:59:16.463
That just is something that
they shouldn't worry about.

00:59:19.290 --> 00:59:21.290
The truce is that students,

00:59:21.290 --> 00:59:24.510
even those whose parents
don't accept evolution,

00:59:24.510 --> 00:59:26.413
need to understand evolution

00:59:26.413 --> 00:59:28.880
in order to be scientifically literate

00:59:29.790 --> 00:59:32.180
and if we can assuage the concerns

00:59:32.180 --> 00:59:34.280
of conservative Christian
parents that indeed,

00:59:34.280 --> 00:59:35.790
no one is telling their children

00:59:35.790 --> 00:59:38.500
that they have to give up
their faith to study science,

00:59:38.500 --> 00:59:42.480
we may be able to teach evolution
with reduced opposition.

00:59:42.480 --> 00:59:46.630
We teach good science at the
college and high school level

00:59:46.630 --> 00:59:50.080
and we leave the door open
to a believing student

00:59:50.080 --> 00:59:52.840
for that student to
engage with that science

00:59:52.840 --> 00:59:54.663
however that student wishes.

00:59:56.040 --> 00:59:59.670
I was talking with a
high school teacher today

00:59:59.670 --> 01:00:01.207
who was a graduate student here

01:00:01.207 --> 01:00:03.969
and he was mentioning,
we were talking about

01:00:03.969 --> 01:00:06.560
how do you deal with the students

01:00:06.560 --> 01:00:07.530
who come into your class

01:00:07.530 --> 01:00:09.640
and the fingers are
wedged tightly in the ear

01:00:09.640 --> 01:00:10.582
because they're afraid

01:00:10.582 --> 01:00:12.988
that they're going to have
to believe in evolution

01:00:12.988 --> 01:00:15.210
when they hear you talk.

01:00:15.210 --> 01:00:17.540
And his solution was one that I've heard

01:00:17.540 --> 01:00:20.340
from many, many teachers and
I think it's very effective.

01:00:20.340 --> 01:00:24.940
His solution was to say, okay,
I just want you to learn it.

01:00:24.940 --> 01:00:26.980
You can accept it or
reject it, that's your call

01:00:26.980 --> 01:00:29.730
but you need to learn it and
you need to pass the test.

01:00:30.770 --> 01:00:32.900
And those weren't his words,

01:00:32.900 --> 01:00:36.140
but you basically can hear the
fingers fly out of the ears

01:00:36.140 --> 01:00:38.150
with a loud popping noise

01:00:38.150 --> 01:00:40.150
because the students all of a sudden go,

01:00:40.150 --> 01:00:41.350
I don't have to believe.

01:00:42.500 --> 01:00:44.780
An interesting thing happens.

01:00:44.780 --> 01:00:45.983
The students find out that evolution

01:00:45.983 --> 01:00:48.140
doesn't actually hurt them.

01:00:48.140 --> 01:00:50.090
Of course, species change through time.

01:00:51.060 --> 01:00:53.950
They find that evolution doesn't mean

01:00:53.950 --> 01:00:54.990
you can't believe in God.

01:00:54.990 --> 01:00:57.750
Evolution means that living
things have common ancestors.

01:00:57.750 --> 01:00:59.612
And look, we can show you the genetic

01:00:59.612 --> 01:01:01.725
and other evolutionary processes

01:01:01.725 --> 01:01:04.750
which bring this change about

01:01:05.620 --> 01:01:07.960
which is a very different
view than they came in.

01:01:07.960 --> 01:01:09.830
But they can't listen to the science

01:01:09.830 --> 01:01:13.350
as long as they've got the
fingers stuck firmly in the ears.

01:01:13.350 --> 01:01:18.350
Getting the fingers out of
the ears is a major need.

01:01:18.610 --> 01:01:21.070
So we on the teaching side of things,

01:01:21.070 --> 01:01:23.835
whether college or K-12,
teach good science,

01:01:23.835 --> 01:01:26.130
leave the door open to students of faith

01:01:26.130 --> 01:01:27.950
to continue believing if they choose.

01:01:27.950 --> 01:01:31.770
It's not the job of the K-12
or the college professor

01:01:31.770 --> 01:01:35.088
to change the religious views of students.

01:01:35.088 --> 01:01:38.950
That said, I've been in the
creation and evolution business

01:01:38.950 --> 01:01:43.560
for long enough to know that
there are no quick fixes.

01:01:43.560 --> 01:01:46.720
We are in this for the long haul.

01:01:46.720 --> 01:01:48.757
The longterm change is
going to take a while

01:01:48.757 --> 01:01:51.890
and so will the short term change.

01:01:51.890 --> 01:01:54.010
And because there aren't any quick fixes,

01:01:54.010 --> 01:01:56.040
the National Center for Science Education

01:01:56.040 --> 01:01:58.090
is in it for the long haul too.

01:01:58.090 --> 01:02:00.910
Please do go to the website ncse.com.

01:02:00.910 --> 01:02:02.690
You're going to find
a lot more information

01:02:02.690 --> 01:02:05.910
on the creation and evolution controversy

01:02:05.910 --> 01:02:08.730
as well as the parallel one
over teaching climate change

01:02:08.730 --> 01:02:11.420
and you'll find some very good suggestions

01:02:11.420 --> 01:02:13.220
for what you can do about it,

01:02:13.220 --> 01:02:16.050
including joining the National
Center for Science Education,

01:02:16.050 --> 01:02:17.930
which I hope you will do.

01:02:17.930 --> 01:02:20.730
Again, children's
stories not withstanding,

01:02:20.730 --> 01:02:22.780
I was very highly honored this year

01:02:22.780 --> 01:02:24.450
to be a Hitchcock lecturer

01:02:24.450 --> 01:02:26.650
and I thank you very much
for coming to hear me

01:02:26.650 --> 01:02:28.340
on this really quite lovely day.

01:02:28.340 --> 01:02:29.338
Thank you.

