01:03:33.100 --> 01:03:37.510
- My special concern are the creationists

01:03:37.510 --> 01:03:39.170
who are professionals,

01:03:39.170 --> 01:03:41.960
particularly those in engineering

01:03:41.960 --> 01:03:43.703
and the medical professions.

01:03:44.690 --> 01:03:48.000
When they put forth in their communities

01:03:48.000 --> 01:03:50.320
against the teaching of evolution,

01:03:50.320 --> 01:03:52.150
they are respected simply because

01:03:52.150 --> 01:03:54.783
they're members of a respected profession.

01:03:55.970 --> 01:03:59.430
Unfortunately, those I have
talked to and listened to,

01:03:59.430 --> 01:04:01.940
do not understand science.

01:04:01.940 --> 01:04:05.070
Many people think that engineering schools

01:04:05.070 --> 01:04:08.293
and medical schools teach science.

01:04:09.790 --> 01:04:14.050
That's becoming true, but traditionally

01:04:14.050 --> 01:04:18.810
that has not been true and
they don't understand science

01:04:18.810 --> 01:04:22.420
and when you try to talk to
them, even your approach,

01:04:22.420 --> 01:04:26.690
they don't give you enough
respect to listen to you.

01:04:26.690 --> 01:04:28.160
So they become an impediment.

01:04:28.160 --> 01:04:31.230
A major impediment to
the kind of reasoning

01:04:31.230 --> 01:04:33.653
that has worked on most lay people.

01:04:34.560 --> 01:04:38.330
What can we do about this impediment?

01:04:38.330 --> 01:04:40.500
- I always think of American Society

01:04:40.500 --> 01:04:43.490
as basically being
divided into three parts,

01:04:43.490 --> 01:04:45.620
like goal I guess.

01:04:45.620 --> 01:04:50.530
There are people like me
who are very convinced

01:04:50.530 --> 01:04:53.370
by the science of evolution
and it takes a whole lot

01:04:53.370 --> 01:04:54.203
to shake that.

01:04:54.203 --> 01:04:56.210
I mean, we're pretty convinced.

01:04:56.210 --> 01:04:57.840
Probably most of the people in this room

01:04:57.840 --> 01:04:59.240
are in that category.

01:04:59.240 --> 01:05:01.180
There are those, like you were describing

01:05:01.180 --> 01:05:04.040
who are very committed anti-evolutionists

01:05:04.040 --> 01:05:08.480
for mostly well religious
reasons of various kinds,

01:05:08.480 --> 01:05:11.040
but most Americans are in the middle.

01:05:11.040 --> 01:05:13.930
They don't think about
science or religion very much

01:05:13.930 --> 01:05:16.010
but they don't belong to denominations

01:05:16.010 --> 01:05:18.980
that require them interpret
the bible literally.

01:05:18.980 --> 01:05:21.330
That is really the target population.

01:05:21.330 --> 01:05:23.278
That is really the group I think

01:05:23.278 --> 01:05:27.070
that it is most useful to
spend your time talking to

01:05:27.070 --> 01:05:30.900
because they are more
open to understanding

01:05:30.900 --> 01:05:33.960
the science and understanding
how science works

01:05:33.960 --> 01:05:36.280
and by the way, I agree with you.

01:05:36.280 --> 01:05:37.680
I concur with you completely

01:05:39.110 --> 01:05:42.210
on the difference between
applied scientists

01:05:42.210 --> 01:05:45.290
like engineers and physicians
versus research scientists.

01:05:45.290 --> 01:05:48.430
The concept of how science
works is really quite different

01:05:48.430 --> 01:05:50.080
in both of those groups

01:05:51.480 --> 01:05:56.480
but let's keep that
group from sliding down

01:05:57.490 --> 01:05:59.100
into the anti evolution side

01:05:59.100 --> 01:06:03.244
and help them understand
what a really wonderful,

01:06:03.244 --> 01:06:07.330
life enriching phenomenon science is

01:06:07.330 --> 01:06:11.350
and evolution within sciences
is a really fascinating field

01:06:11.350 --> 01:06:14.080
and communicating some of that excitement

01:06:14.080 --> 01:06:16.580
I think can help keep that middle group

01:06:16.580 --> 01:06:20.790
from absorbing some of
the erroneous information

01:06:20.790 --> 01:06:25.410
that is being produced
by this group down here.

